225 | ## Quality Validation
226 | 
227 | ### File Coverage Checking Algorithm
228 | 
229 | `validate_codebase_brain.py` implements three-phase validation:
230 | 
231 | ```python
232 | def validate(self) -> ValidationResult:
233 |     # Phase 1: File Coverage
234 |     file_paths = extract_file_paths()  # Regex: `filename.ext`
235 |     files_exist = check_existence(file_paths)
236 |     coverage_pct = files_exist / total * 100
237 |     
238 |     # Phase 2: Line Reference Validation
239 |     line_refs = extract_line_references()  # Regex: "line 123"
240 |     valid_refs = validate_line_numbers(line_refs)
241 |     accuracy_pct = valid_refs / total * 100
242 |     
243 |     # Phase 3: Drift Detection
244 |     staleness = calculate_drift()  # Time-based
245 |     drift_passed = staleness < 15.0
246 |     
247 |     return ValidationResult(...)
248 | ```
249 | 
250 | **File Coverage Algorithm:**
251 | 
252 | ```mermaid
253 | graph TD
254 |     A[Parse AGENTS.md] --> B[Extract File Paths]
255 |     B --> C{Regex Match}
256 |     C -->|Header| D[#### `file.ext`]
257 |     C -->|Inline| E[`path/to/file.ext`]
258 |     D --> F[Validate Existence]
259 |     E --> F
260 |     F --> G{File Exists?}
261 |     G -->|Yes| H[Coverage++]
262 |     G -->|No| I[Missing List]
263 |     H --> J[Calculate %]
264 |     I --> J
265 | ```
266 | 
267 | **Regex Patterns:**
268 | ```python
269 | # Pattern 1: Markdown headers
270 | r'####?\s+`([^`]+\.[a-zA-Z0-9]+)`'
271 | 
272 | # Pattern 2: Inline code with paths
273 | r'`([a-zA-Z0-9_/-]+\.[a-zA-Z0-9]+)`'
274 | ```
275 | 
276 | **Coverage Thresholds:**
277 | - **Green:** 95-100% (all files exist)
278 | - **Yellow:** 85-94% (minor drift)
279 | - **Red:** <85% (significant drift, update required)
280 | 
281 | ### Line Reference Validation Methodology
282 | 
283 | **Challenge:** AGENTS.md references specific line numbers (e.g., "line 193 has duplicate friction tags"). Files change, line numbers drift.
284 | 
285 | **Solution:** Context-aware line validation
286 | 
287 | ```python
288 | def validate_line_references(self, line_refs: List[Dict]) -> Tuple[int, List[Dict]]:
289 |     for ref in line_refs:
290 |         file_path = workspace / ref['file']
291 |         
292 |         if not file_path.exists():
293 |             stale_refs.append({**ref, 'reason': 'file_not_found'})
294 |             continue
295 |         
296 |         lines = file_path.read_text().split('\n')
297 |         
298 |         if ref['referenced_line'] <= len(lines):
299 |             valid_refs += 1
300 |         else:
301 |             stale_refs.append({
302 |                 **ref, 
303 |                 'reason': 'line_out_of_range',
304 |                 'actual_lines': len(lines)
305 |             })
306 |     
307 |     return valid_refs, stale_refs
308 | ```
309 | 
310 | **Context Extraction:**
311 | - Searches ±5 lines around line reference in AGENTS.md
312 | - Extracts associated file path from nearby context
313 | - Validates line number against actual file length
314 | 
315 | **Validation Output:**
316 | ```json
317 | {
318 |   "total_line_refs": 47,
319 |   "valid_line_refs": 45,
320 |   "stale_line_refs": [
321 |     {
322 |       "agents_line": 149,
323 |       "referenced_line": 193,
324 |       "file": "worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf",
325 |       "reason": "line_out_of_range",
326 |       "actual_lines": 180
327 |     }
328 |   ],
329 |   "line_accuracy_percentage": 95.7
330 | }
331 | ```
332 | 
333 | ### Drift Detection Strategy
334 | 
335 | **Drift Definition:** Staleness of AGENTS.md relative to codebase changes
336 | 
337 | **Algorithm:**
338 | ```python
339 | def calculate_drift(self) -> float:
340 |     agents_mtime = get_modification_time('AGENTS.md')
341 |     newest_mtime = max(get_modification_time(f) for f in repo_files)
342 |     
343 |     if newest_mtime > agents_mtime:
344 |         time_diff_days = (newest_mtime - agents_mtime).days
345 |         staleness = min(100.0, time_diff_days * 10)  # 1 day = 10%
346 |     else:
347 |         staleness = 0.0
348 |     
349 |     return staleness
350 | ```
351 | 
352 | **Drift Thresholds:**
353 | - **0-5%:** Fresh (updated within 12 hours)
354 | - **5-15%:** Acceptable (updated within 1.5 days)
355 | - **15-30%:** Stale (update recommended)
356 | - **>30%:** Critical (update required)
357 | 
358 | **Drift Visualization:**
359 | 
360 | ```mermaid
361 | graph LR
362 |     A[Code Change] -->|Triggers| B[CI/CD]
363 |     B -->|Runs| C[validate_codebase_brain.py]
364 |     C -->|Checks| D{Drift < 15%?}
365 |     D -->|Yes| E[Pass]
366 |     D -->|No| F[Fail Build]
367 |     F -->|Alerts| G[Update AGENTS.md]
368 | ```
369 | 
370 | **Integration Points:**
371 | - **Pre-commit hook:** Warn if drift >10%
372 | - **CI/CD pipeline:** Fail build if drift >15%
373 | - **Scheduled job:** Weekly validation report
