445 | **Recommendation:** For repos >300 files, use **hierarchical AGENTS.md**:
446 | ```
447 | AGENTS.md (master)
448 | ├── AGENTS-backend.md
449 | ├── AGENTS-frontend.md
450 | ├── AGENTS-infrastructure.md
451 | └── AGENTS-data.md
452 | ```
453 | 
454 | ### Memory and Performance Considerations
455 | 
456 | **Memory Usage:**
457 | 
458 | ```python
459 | # validate_codebase_brain.py memory profile
460 | Base Memory:           15 MB
461 | Per File Loaded:       0.5 MB
462 | Per Line Reference:    0.1 KB
463 | 
464 | 30-file codebase:      30 MB
465 | 500-file codebase:     265 MB
466 | ```
467 | 
468 | **Performance Bottlenecks:**
469 | 
470 | 1. **File I/O:** Dominant cost at scale
471 |    - **Solution:** Parallel file reading with `concurrent.futures`
472 |    - **Speedup:** 3-4x on multi-core systems
473 | 
474 | 2. **Regex Matching:** O(n×m) where n=lines, m=patterns
475 |    - **Solution:** Compile regex patterns once
476 |    - **Speedup:** 2x
477 | 
478 | 3. **Drift Detection:** Full repository scan
479 |    - **Solution:** Git-based change detection (only scan modified files)
480 |    - **Speedup:** 10-100x depending on change frequency
481 | 
482 | **Optimized Validation Algorithm:**
483 | 
484 | ```python
485 | def validate_optimized(self, changed_files: Set[str] = None):
486 |     # Only validate changed files if provided
487 |     if changed_files:
488 |         file_paths = {f for f in extract_file_paths() if f in changed_files}
489 |     else:
490 |         file_paths = extract_file_paths()
491 |     
492 |     # Parallel file validation
493 |     with ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=8) as executor:
494 |         results = executor.map(validate_file, file_paths)
495 |     
496 |     return aggregate_results(results)
497 | ```
498 | 
499 | **Expected Performance (500-file repo):**
500 | - **Full Validation:** 4.5s
501 | - **Incremental (10 changed files):** 0.4s
502 | - **CI/CD Impact:** Negligible (<5s added to build)
503 | 
