165 |   - AHRS_EKF_TYPE=10 (EKF3 enabled)
166 |   - Rover-specific attitude control params
167 |   - Servo output configuration
168 | - **Breaking Changes:**
169 |   - Changing EKF params affects attitude estimation
170 |   - AHRS_ORIENTATION must match Gazebo coordinate transform
171 | - **GOTCHA:** Large file, use line ranges when reading
172 | 
173 | ### `/scripts/`
174 | 
175 | #### `balance_controller.py`
176 | - **Purpose:** Simple standing balance controller
177 | - **Algorithm:** PID on pitch (Kp=2.0, Ki=0.01, Kd=0.5)
178 | - **Control:** Hip pitch (primary) + ankle pitch (secondary, 0.5x)
179 | - **Standing Pose:** hip=-0.09, knee=0.35, ankle=0.0
180 | - **Breaking Changes:**
181 |   - Gains tuned for current mass distribution
182 |   - Standing pose must match world file initial_position
183 | - **GOTCHA:** Stronger gains than gait controller
184 | 
185 | #### `gait_controller.py`
186 | - **Purpose:** 6-phase walking gait with balance
187 | - **Algorithm:**
188 |   - Balance PID (Kp=0.08, Ki=0.001, Kd=0.01) - weaker than balance_controller
189 |   - 6 gait phases: STAND → SHIFT_R → STEP_L → STAND → SHIFT_L → STEP_R
190 |   - Phase duration: 3.0s each
191 |   - Step parameters: HIP_STEP=0.05, KNEE_LIFT=0.55
192 | - **Startup Sequence:**
193 |   1. Pre-hold pose 40x before MAVLink (prevents fall during connection)
194 |   2. Connect to MAVLink
195 |   3. Kill startup.sh
196 |   4. Hold pose 20x
197 |   5. Calibrate standing pitch (20 samples)
198 |   6. Stabilize 3s with balance
199 |   7. Execute gait phases
200 | - **Breaking Changes:**
201 |   - Phase timing affects stability
202 |   - Balance gains must be tuned with gait parameters
203 | - **GOTCHA:** Resets balance integral between stabilize and gait phases
204 | 
205 | #### `zmp_gait_controller.py`
206 | - **Purpose:** Advanced ZMP preview control walking (INCOMPLETE)
207 | - **Algorithm:**
208 |   - LIPM (Linear Inverted Pendulum Model)
209 |   - Preview horizon: 20 steps
210 |   - Step length: 0.12m, duration: 0.6s
211 |   - Double support: 0.1s
212 | - **Dependencies:**
213 |   - preview_control.py (LIPM controller)
214 |   - foot.py (swing trajectory)
215 |   - inverse_kinematics.py (leg IK)
216 | - **Breaking Changes:** CRITICAL - requires hip_roll joints not in current model
217 | - **GOTCHA:** Hardcoded path `/home/neetamis/...` (line 6) - will break on other systems
218 | 
219 | #### `inverse_kinematics.py`
220 | - **Purpose:** 2-link leg IK solver
221 | - **Algorithm:**
222 |   - Geometric IK for planar 2R manipulator
223 |   - L1=L2=0.20m (thigh/shin lengths)
224 |   - Ankle compensation: ankle = -(hip_pitch + knee*0.3)
225 | - **Joint Limits:**
226 |   - hip_pitch: [-1.57, 0.52] rad (-90° to +30°)
227 |   - knee: [0.0, 2.618] rad (0° to +150°)
228 |   - ankle: [-0.5, 0.5] rad
229 |   - hip_roll: [-0.4, 0.4] rad
230 | - **Breaking Changes:**
231 |   - Leg lengths must match SDF model
232 |   - Joint limits must match SDF
233 | - **GOTCHA:** Assumes hip joint at CoM height, foot at ground
234 | 
235 | #### `preview_control.py`
236 | - **Purpose:** LIPM preview controller implementation
237 | - **Algorithm:**
238 |   - Discrete-time LQR with preview
239 |   - Solves discrete algebraic Riccati equation
240 |   - Computes preview gains for N-step horizon
241 | - **Parameters:**
242 |   - dt=0.02s, com_height=0.35m, preview_horizon=20
243 |   - Qe=1.0 (tracking weight), R=1e-6 (control weight)
244 | - **Breaking Changes:**
245 |   - CoM height must match robot geometry
246 |   - Preview horizon affects computational cost
247 | - **GOTCHA:** Requires scipy for solve_discrete_are
248 | 
249 | #### `foot.py`
250 | - **Purpose:** Swing foot trajectory generation
251 | - **Algorithm:**
252 |   - Sinusoidal height profile: z = h*sin(π*phase)
253 |   - Linear x progression
254 |   - Constant y (lateral position)
255 | - **Parameters:**
256 |   - max_height=0.04m (swing clearance)
257 |   - duration=0.6s
258 | - **Breaking Changes:** Height must clear ground obstacles
259 | 
260 | #### `hold_pose.py`
261 | - **Purpose:** Simple pose holder (UNUSED)
262 | - **Pose:** hip=-0.05, knee=0.1, ankle=0.05
263 | - **GOTCHA:** Different pose than gait_controller standing pose
264 | 
265 | #### `startup.sh`
266 | - **Purpose:** Hold standing pose until gait controller starts
267 | - **Pose:** hip=-0.09, knee=0.35, ankle=0.0 (matches gait_controller)
268 | - **Usage:** Run in background, killed by gait_controller after MAVLink connection
269 | - **Breaking Changes:** Pose must match gait controller exactly
270 | 
271 | #### `startup_hold.py`
272 | - **Purpose:** Python version of startup pose holder
273 | - **Pose:** All joints to 0.0 (DIFFERENT from startup.sh)
274 | - **GOTCHA:** Inconsistent with other startup scripts
275 | 
276 | #### `startup_lock.py`
277 | - **Purpose:** Lock joints immediately after Gazebo starts
278 | - **Pose:** hip=-0.10, knee=0.30, ankle=0.10
279 | - **Usage:** Run once, exits after 30 iterations (1.5s)
280 | - **GOTCHA:** Yet another different standing pose
281 | 
282 | #### `startup_pose.sh`
283 | - **Purpose:** Bash version of startup lock
284 | - **Pose:** hip=-0.2, knee=0.4
285 | - **GOTCHA:** More aggressive pose than others
286 | 
287 | #### `launch.sh`
288 | - **Purpose:** Instructions for manual 3-terminal launch
289 | - **GOTCHA:** References ArduCopter instead of Rover (outdated)
290 | 
291 | #### `start_all.sh`
292 | - **Purpose:** Kill all processes and show manual launch instructions
293 | - **GOTCHA:** Also references ArduCopter (outdated)
294 | 
295 | #### `calculate_com.py`
296 | - **Purpose:** Calculate center of mass from URDF
297 | - **GOTCHA:** References `humanoid_proto.urdf` which doesn't exist (SDF model only)
298 | 
299 | #### `validate_inertia.py`
300 | - **Purpose:** Advanced CoM validator with joint transforms
301 | - **Features:**
302 |   - Builds kinematic tree
303 |   - Computes world-frame CoM
304 |   - Validates inertia triangle inequality
305 |   - Checks ODE stability floor (1e-4 kg·m²)
306 | - **GOTCHA:** Also references non-existent URDF file
307 | 
308 | #### `check_config.py`
309 | - **Purpose:** Verify Gazebo joint topics have subscribers
310 | - **Topics Checked:**
311 |   - /l_hip_pitch/cmd
312 |   - /r_hip_pitch/cmd
313 |   - /l_knee/cmd
314 |   - /r_knee/cmd
315 |   - /l_ankle/cmd
316 |   - /r_ankle/cmd
317 | - **Usage:** Diagnostic tool to verify Gazebo plugin loaded correctly
318 | 
319 | #### `print_tree.py`
320 | - **Purpose:** Print URDF kinematic tree
321 | - **GOTCHA:** References non-existent URDF file
322 | 
323 | ### `/terrain/`
324 | 
325 | #### `S36E149.DAT`
326 | - **Purpose:** Terrain elevation data (likely unused)
327 | - **Safe to delete:** Probably, but keep for future terrain features
328 | 
329 | ---
330 | 
331 | ## 🔧 Non-Obvious Patterns & Gotchas
332 | 
333 | ### 1. **Multiple Standing Poses**
334 | **Problem:** 5 different standing poses across scripts:
335 | - `gait_controller.py`: hip=-0.09, knee=0.35
336 | - `startup.sh`: hip=-0.09, knee=0.35 ✅ (matches gait)
337 | - `startup_lock.py`: hip=-0.10, knee=0.30
338 | - `startup_pose.sh`: hip=-0.2, knee=0.4
339 | - `hold_pose.py`: hip=-0.05, knee=0.1
340 | 
341 | **Solution:** Use `gait_controller.py` pose as canonical. Others are experimental.
342 | 
343 | ### 2. **ArduPilot Plugin PWM Conversion**
344 | **Formula:** `angle = (pwm - 1500) / 500 * multiplier + offset`
345 | 
346 | **Example (l_hip_pitch):**
347 | - PWM range: [1000, 2000]
348 | - multiplier: 1.571
349 | - offset: -0.5
350 | - PWM 1000 → angle = -1.571 - 0.5 = -2.071 rad (clamped to -1.571)
351 | - PWM 1500 → angle = 0.0 - 0.5 = -0.5 rad
352 | - PWM 2000 → angle = 1.571 - 0.5 = 1.071 rad (clamped to 0.523)
353 | 
354 | **GOTCHA:** Offset shifts neutral point, not just range!
355 | 
356 | ### 3. **Python Controllers Bypass ArduPilot**
357 | **Current:** Python → Gazebo topics directly
358 | **Intended:** Python → MAVLink → ArduPilot → Gazebo
359 | 
360 | **Why:** Faster development, but defeats purpose of ArduPilot integration.
361 | 
362 | ### 4. **Ankle Joints Are Fixed**
363 | **SDF:** `<joint name="l_ankle" type="fixed">`
364 | **Controllers:** Still send commands to `/l_ankle/cmd`
365 | 
366 | **Impact:** Ankle commands ignored, but IK solver includes ankle compensation.
367 | 
368 | ### 5. **Duplicate Friction Tags**
369 | **Location:** `worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf` lines 193, 201, 209, 220, 228, 236
370 | **Code:** `<friction>1.5</friction><friction>0.5</friction>`
371 | 
372 | **Impact:** Gazebo uses last value (0.5). First value ignored.
373 | 
374 | ### 6. **Initial Pitch Lean**
375 | **World file:** `<pose>0 0 0.57 0.12 0 0</pose>` (0.12 rad = 6.9° forward pitch)
376 | 
377 | **Purpose:** Compensates for CoM position, prevents backward fall on spawn.
378 | 
379 | **GOTCHA:** If you change mass distribution, must retune this value.
380 | 
381 | ### 7. **Balance Integral Windup**
382 | **Problem:** `gait_controller.py` resets integral between stabilize and gait phases (lines 97-98)
383 | 
384 | **Why:** Prevents carry-over of accumulated error from standing to walking.
385 | 
386 | **GOTCHA:** If you remove this, robot will lurch on first step.
387 | 
388 | ### 8. **ZMP Controller Missing Joints**
389 | **Problem:** `zmp_gait_controller.py` requires hip_roll joints
390 | **Reality:** Current model only has hip_pitch
391 | 
392 | **Impact:** ZMP controller cannot run on current model.
393 | 
394 | **Fix Required:** Add hip_roll joints to SDF model, or remove hip_roll from ZMP controller.
395 | 
396 | ### 9. **Hardcoded Paths**
397 | **Location:** `zmp_gait_controller.py` line 6
398 | **Code:** `sys.path.insert(0, '/home/neetamis/humanoid-ardupilot-sitl/scripts')`
399 | 
400 | **Impact:** Breaks on any other system.
401 | 
402 | **Fix:** Use relative imports or `os.path.dirname(__file__)`.
403 | 
404 | ### 10. **Coordinate Frame Transforms**
405 | **ArduPilotPlugin:**
406 | - `modelXYZToAirplaneXForwardZDown`: 0 0 0 180 0 0
407 | - `gazeboXYZToNED`: 0 0 0 180 0 90
408 | 
409 | **Purpose:** Convert between Gazebo (X-forward, Z-up) and ArduPilot (X-forward, Z-down, NED frame).
410 | 
411 | **GOTCHA:** If you change these, IMU data will be wrong and robot will fall.
412 | 
413 | ---
414 | 
415 | ## ⚠️ Known Failure Modes
416 | 
417 | ### 1. **Robot Falls Immediately on Spawn**
418 | **Cause:** Initial pose doesn't match standing pose, or startup.sh not running
419 | **Fix:** 
420 | - Ensure world file initial_position matches gait controller standing pose
421 | - Run `startup.sh` in background before starting gait controller
422 | - Check initial pitch lean (0.12 rad) is correct for CoM
423 | 
424 | ### 2. **Robot Explodes (Joints Fly Apart)**
425 | **Cause:** Physics timestep too large, or joint limits violated
426 | **Fix:**
427 | - Keep max_step_size ≤ 0.004s
428 | - Check joint commands within limits
429 | - Increase joint damping if oscillating
430 | 
431 | ### 3. **Gait Controller Connects But Robot Doesn't Move**
432 | **Cause:** Gazebo topics not subscribed (plugin not loaded)
433 | **Fix:**
434 | - Run `check_config.py` to verify topics
435 | - Restart Gazebo if topics missing
436 | - Check ArduPilotPlugin loaded in world file
437 | 
438 | ### 4. **Balance Controller Oscillates**
439 | **Cause:** PID gains too high, or derivative kick
440 | **Fix:**
441 | - Reduce Kp (currently 2.0 in balance_controller, 0.08 in gait_controller)
442 | - Add derivative filtering
443 | - Increase damping in joint dynamics
444 | 
445 | ### 5. **Walking Gait Unstable**
446 | **Cause:** Multiple factors
447 | - Phase timing too fast (3.0s is very slow)
448 | - Step length too large (0.05 rad hip displacement)
449 | - Balance gains too weak (Kp=0.08)
450 | - No ZMP stability margin
451 | 
452 | **Fix:**
453 | - Implement proper ZMP preview control
454 | - Add hip_roll joints for lateral balance
455 | - Tune gait parameters empirically
456 | - Increase balance PID gains during swing phase
457 | 
458 | ### 6. **MAVLink Connection Timeout**
459 | **Cause:** ArduPilot not outputting to UDP:14551
460 | **Fix:**
461 | - In MAVProxy: `output add 127.0.0.1:14551`
462 | - Or use `--out=udp:127.0.0.1:14551` in sim_vehicle.py
463 | 
464 | ### 7. **ZMP Controller Import Error**
465 | **Cause:** Hardcoded path doesn't exist
466 | **Fix:** Change line 6 to relative import or correct path
467 | 
468 | ### 8. **Foot Slipping**
469 | **Cause:** Friction coefficient too low
470 | **Fix:** Increase `<mu>` in foot collision (currently 1.0, try 1.5-2.0)
471 | 
472 | ### 9. **Knee Hyperextension**
473 | **Cause:** IK solver allows knee < 0
474 | **Fix:** Already clamped in inverse_kinematics.py (line 17), but check commands
475 | 
476 | ### 10. **ArduPilot EKF Not Converging**
477 | **Cause:** IMU data quality or coordinate transform wrong
478 | **Fix:**
479 | - Check `AHRS_EKF_TYPE=10` (EKF3)
480 | - Verify coordinate transforms in ArduPilotPlugin
481 | - Check IMU sensor update_rate (1000 Hz)
482 | 
483 | ---
484 | 
485 | ## 📈 Current Status & Next Steps
486 | 
487 | ### ✅ What Works
488 | 1. Gazebo simulation loads and runs stably
489 | 2. Robot model physics (mass, inertia, collisions)
490 | 3. ArduPilot SITL connects via JSON protocol
491 | 4. IMU data flows: Gazebo → ArduPilot → MAVLink
492 | 5. EKF3 attitude estimation (pitch, roll, yaw)
493 | 6. Balance controller maintains standing pose
494 | 7. Gait controller executes 6-phase walking cycle (but unstable)
495 | 8. Joint position control via Gazebo topics
496 | 9. Startup scripts prevent fall during initialization
497 | 
498 | ### ⚠️ What's Incomplete
499 | 1. Walking gait not stable (falls after 1-2 steps)
500 | 2. ZMP preview controller missing hip_roll joints
501 | 3. No lateral (roll) balance control
502 | 4. Lua scripting not integrated
503 | 5. ArduPilot servo output not used (Python bypasses it)
504 | 6. No MAVLink command interface (GUIDED mode, waypoints)
505 | 
506 | ### ❌ What Doesn't Work
507 | 1. Autonomous walking for >3 steps
508 | 2. MAVLink waypoint navigation
509 | 3. ZMP controller (requires model changes)
510 | 4. Lua gait generation
511 | 5. ArduPilot-controlled locomotion
512 | 
513 | ### 🎯 Next Steps (Priority Order)
514 | 
515 | 1. **Add Hip Roll Joints**
516 |    - Modify `worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf`
517 |    - Add l_hip_roll, r_hip_roll revolute joints
518 |    - Update ArduPilotPlugin channel mapping (CH4, CH5)
519 |    - Update IK solver to include roll
520 | 
521 | 2. **Stabilize Walking Gait**
522 |    - Implement ZMP stability margin check
523 |    - Add lateral balance (hip roll control)
524 |    - Tune gait timing (reduce from 3.0s to 0.6-1.0s)
525 |    - Increase balance PID gains during swing phase
526 | 
527 | 3. **Integrate Lua Scripting**
528 |    - Port gait_controller.py logic to Lua
529 |    - Use SRV_Channels for servo output
530 |    - Test ArduPilot → Gazebo control loop
531 |    - Remove Python bypass
532 | 
533 | 4. **Implement MAVLink Control**
534 |    - Add GUIDED mode handler in Lua
535 |    - Convert velocity commands to gait parameters
536 |    - Implement waypoint following
537 |    - Add AUTO mode support
538 | 
539 | 5. **Optimize Performance**
540 |    - Profile control loop timing
541 |    - Reduce Gazebo topic latency
542 |    - Tune PID gains for faster response
543 |    - Add feedforward terms
544 | 
545 | ---
546 | 
547 | ## 🔍 Quick Reference
548 | 
549 | ### Standing Pose (Canonical)
550 | ```python
551 | HIP_STAND  = -0.09  # rad
552 | KNEE_STAND =  0.35  # rad
553 | ANKLE_STAND = 0.0   # rad (fixed joint)
554 | ```
555 | 
556 | ### Joint Limits (SDF)
557 | ```
558 | l_hip_pitch:  [-1.571, 0.523] rad  (-90° to +30°)
559 | l_knee:       [0.0, 2.618] rad     (0° to +150°)
560 | l_knee_shin:  [0.0, 2.618] rad     (0° to +150°)
561 | l_ankle:      fixed
562 | ```
563 | 
564 | ### Robot Geometry
565 | ```
566 | Total Mass:    3.9 kg
567 | Torso:         2.5 kg
568 | Thigh (each):  0.5 kg
569 | Shin (each):   0.3 kg
570 | Foot (each):   0.15 kg
571 | Leg Length:    L1=L2=0.20m
572 | Foot Width:    0.16m (hip separation)
573 | CoM Height:    ~0.38m above ground
574 | ```
575 | 
576 | ### Network Ports
